  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Gill's Exposition of the Entire Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Let all those that seek thee,.... The Targum is, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "\"that seek doctrine (or instruction) from thee.'' ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "rejoice and be glad in thee; the Targum paraphrases it, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "\"rejoice and be glad in thy word.'' ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and let such as love thy salvation say continually, let God be magnified; the Targum is, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "\"let the glory of the Lord be increased;'' ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and in Psalm 40:16, instead of \"God\", it is \"the Lord\", or \"Jehovah\": See Gill on Psalm 40:16. ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "and in ",
            "children": []
